enum.name: AdmState
enum.description: The administrative state of a resource.

enumMember.name: LOCKED
enumMember.description: The resource is administratively prohibited from performing services for its users.

enumMember.name: UNLOCKED
enumMember.description: The resource is administratively permitted to perform services for its users. This is independent of its inherent operability.

enumMember.name: SHUTTINGDOWN
enumMember.description: Use of the resource is administratively permitted to existing instances of use only. While the system remains in the shutting down state the manager may at any time cause the managed object to revert to the locked state.

enumMember.name: FEATURE_NOT_ACTIVATED
enumMember.description: Assisted time holdover not activated.

enumMember.name: NO_ASSISTING_REF_QUALIFIED
enumMember.description: Assisted time holdover activated. No assisting reference qualified to assist.

enumMember.name: ASSISTANCE_NOT_ACTIVE
enumMember.description: Assisted time holdover activated. Ordinary time synchronization reference active.

enumMember.name: NO_FAULT
enumMember.description: Assisting reference has been evaluated and is able to assist in case of primary time synchronization failure.

enumMember.name: UNKNOWN
enumMember.description: Status information not available.

enumMember.name: ASSISTING_REFERENCE_MONITORED
enumMember.description: Assisting reference is monitored. Not ready to assist.

enumMember.name: QL_TOO_LOW
enumMember.description: Quality level too low to improve time holdover performance.

enumMember.name: PTP_FAULT
enumMember.description: Corresponding BoundaryOrdinaryClock MO and or PtpBcOcPort MO faulty. Check status attribute on these MOs to identify specific fault.

enum.name: AvailStatus
enum.description: The availability status is used to qualify the operational state. It indicates why the operational state has changed its value.

enumMember.name: IN_TEST
enumMember.description: The resource is undergoing a test procedure. If the administrative state is locked or shutting down then normal users are precluded from using the resource.

enumMember.name: FAILED
enumMember.description: The resource has an internal fault that prevents it from operating.

enumMember.name: POWER_OFF
enumMember.description: The resource requires power to be applied and is not powered on.

enumMember.name: OFF_LINE
enumMember.description: The resource requires a routine operation to be performed. This routine operation is to place the resource online and make it available for use. The operation may be manual or automatic, or both. The operational state is disabled.

enumMember.name: OFF_DUTY
enumMember.description: The resource has been made inactive by an internal control process.

enumMember.name: DEPENDENCY
enumMember.description: The resource cannot operate because some other resource on which it depends is unavailable.

enumMember.name: DEGRADED
enumMember.description: The service available from the resource is degraded in some respect.

enumMember.name: NOT_INSTALLED
enumMember.description: The resource represented by the managed object is not present, or is incomplete.

enumMember.name: LOG_FULL
enumMember.description: This indicates a log full condition.

enumMember.name: DEPENDENCY_LOCKED
enumMember.description: The administrative state of a resource that this resource depends on is locked. or the availability status of the other resource is dependency locked.

enumMember.name: DEPENDENCY_FAILED
enumMember.description: The availability status of a resource that this resource depends on is failed or dependency failed.

enumMember.name: DEPENDENCY_SHUTTINGDOWN
enumMember.description: The administrative state of a resource that this resource depends on is shutting down. or the availability status of the other resource is dependency shutting down.

enumMember.name: NOT_ACTIVATED_AS_NODE_GROUP_MEMBER
enumMember.description: Node is not activated as Node Group Member.

enumMember.name: ROLE_NOT_DEFINED
enumMember.description: Node is configured as Node Group Member, and that role is not defined.

enumMember.name: SYNC_PROVIDER
enumMember.description: Node is in Synchronization Provider role within Node Group.

enumMember.name: SYNC_RECEIVER
enumMember.description: Node is in Synchronization Receiver role within Node Group, and in contact with Synchronization Provider in same Node Group.

enumMember.name: ENABLED

class.name: AssistingReference
class.description:
Represents a time holdover assisting synchronization reference for radio equipment clock.
Dependencies: Two or more AssistingReference MOs cannot refer to same BoundaryOrdinaryClock MO.

validationRules.rule: <schema xmlns="http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron"> <pattern> <rule> <assert test='every $assistingReferenceId in @assistingReferenceId satisfies (every $encapsulation in @encapsulation satisfies (count(../AssistingReference[contains($encapsulation, "BoundaryOrdinaryClock=") and ($assistingReferenceId ne @assistingReferenceId) and ($encapsulation eq @encapsulation)]) eq 0))'> <value-of select="."/> Two or more AssistingReference MOs cannot refer to same BoundaryOrdinaryClock MO.</assert> <assert test='every $encapsulation in @encapsulation satisfies (contains(@encapsulation, "BoundaryOrdinaryClock=") and (($encapsulation/@clockType eq 2) and ($encapsulation/@ptpProfile eq 4))) or not(exists(@encapsulation))'><value-of select="."/> AssistingReference MO can only refer to BoundaryOrdinaryClock MO whose attributes clockType is SLAVE_ONLY_ORDINARY_CLOCK and ptpProfile is G_8275_2.</assert> </rule> </pattern> </schema>

class.dependenciesScript: <schema xmlns="http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron"> <pattern> <rule> <assert test='every $assistingReferenceId in @assistingReferenceId satisfies (every $encapsulation in @encapsulation satisfies (count(../AssistingReference[contains($encapsulation, "BoundaryOrdinaryClock=") and ($assistingReferenceId ne @assistingReferenceId) and ($encapsulation eq @encapsulation)]) eq 0))'> <value-of select="."/> Two or more AssistingReference MOs cannot refer to same BoundaryOrdinaryClock MO.</assert> <assert test='every $encapsulation in @encapsulation satisfies (contains(@encapsulation, "BoundaryOrdinaryClock=") and (($encapsulation/@clockType eq 2) and ($encapsulation/@ptpProfile eq 4))) or not(exists(@encapsulation))'><value-of select="."/> AssistingReference MO can only refer to BoundaryOrdinaryClock MO whose attributes clockType is SLAVE_ONLY_ORDINARY_CLOCK and ptpProfile is G_8275_2.</assert> </rule> </pattern> </schema>

attribute.name: bfnOffset
attribute.description:
Offsets BFN from default position as calculated from the time synchronization reference.
Positive offset means BFN is advanced. Negative offset means BFN is delayed.

attribute.name: clockOperQuality
attribute.description: Operational quality of selected synchronization reference.

attribute.name: clockSettledQuality
attribute.description: Settled quality of RadioEquipmentClock MO.

attribute.name: currentAssistingReference
attribute.description:
Currently selected assisting reference for time synchronization.
Empty if no assisting reference is selected.

attribute.name: currentRadioClockReference
attribute.description: Currently selected reference to RadioEquipmentClock MO, is empty if no clock reference is selected.

attribute.name: freqDeviationThreshold
attribute.description: Maximum frequency deviation threshold accepted for external synchronization references.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute causes traffic disturbances.

attribute.name: minQualityLevel
attribute.description: Minimum quality level for telecom standard options, that is required for a source to be accepted as active synchronization reference.
attribute.dependencies: If telecomStandard attribute in Synchronization MO is changed, minQualityLevel is changed to quality level value defined within selected telecom standard.

attribute.description: Role of node as Node Group Member.

attribute.name: radioClockPriorityTable

attribute.description: State of RadioEquipmentClock MO.

attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: selectionProcessMode
attribute.description: Whether quality processing is enabled.

attribute.name: timeSyncAssistanceState
attribute.description: Time synchronization assistance state.

class.name: RadioEquipmentClockReference
class.description:
Represents generic synchronization reference for radio equipment clock.
Specific interface or protocol reference can use, is configured by encapsulation attribute.
Dependencies: Two or more RadioEquipmentClockReference MOs cannot have same priority.

validationRules.rule: <schema xmlns="http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron"> <pattern> <rule> <assert test='every $radioEquipmentClockReferenceId in @radioEquipmentClockReferenceId satisfies (every $priority in @priority satisfies (count(../RadioEquipmentClockReference[($radioEquipmentClockReferenceId ne @radioEquipmentClockReferenceId) and ($priority eq @priority)]) eq 0))'> <value-of select="."/> Two or more RadioEquipmentClockReference MOs cannot have same priority.</assert> <assert test='every $radioEquipmentClockReferenceId in @radioEquipmentClockReferenceId satisfies (every $encapsulation in @encapsulation satisfies (count(../RadioEquipmentClockReference[contains($encapsulation, "FrequencySyncIO=") and ($radioEquipmentClockReferenceId ne @radioEquipmentClockReferenceId) and ($encapsulation eq @encapsulation)]) eq 0))'> <value-of select="."/> Two or more RadioEquipmentClockReference MOs cannot refer to same FrequencySyncIO MO in attribute encapsulation.</assert> <assert test='every $radioEquipmentClockReferenceId in @radioEquipmentClockReferenceId satisfies (every $encapsulation in @encapsulation satisfies (count(../RadioEquipmentClockReference[contains($encapsulation, "TimeSyncIO=") and ($radioEquipmentClockReferenceId ne @radioEquipmentClockReferenceId) and ($encapsulation eq @encapsulation)]) eq 0))'> <value-of select="."/> Two or more RadioEquipmentClockReference MOs cannot refer to same TimeSyncIO MO in attribute encapsulation.</assert> <assert test='every $radioEquipmentClockReferenceId in @radioEquipmentClockReferenceId satisfies (every $encapsulation in @encapsulation satisfies (count(../RadioEquipmentClockReference[contains($encapsulation, "SyncEthInput=") and ($radioEquipmentClockReferenceId ne @radioEquipmentClockReferenceId) and ($encapsulation eq @encapsulation)]) eq 0))'> <value-of select="."/> Two or more RadioEquipmentClockReference MOs cannot refer to same SyncEthInput MO in attribute encapsulation.</assert> <assert test='every $radioEquipmentClockReferenceId in @radioEquipmentClockReferenceId satisfies (every $encapsulation in @encapsulation satisfies (count(../RadioEquipmentClockReference[contains($encapsulation, "BoundaryOrdinaryClock=") and ($radioEquipmentClockReferenceId ne @radioEquipmentClockReferenceId) and ($encapsulation eq @encapsulation)]) eq 0))'> <value-of select="."/> Two or more RadioEquipmentClockReference MOs cannot refer to same BoundaryOrdinaryClock MO in attribute encapsulation.</assert> <assert test='every $radioEquipmentClockReferenceId in @radioEquipmentClockReferenceId satisfies (every $encapsulation in @encapsulation satisfies (count(../RadioEquipmentClockReference[contains($encapsulation, "NtpFrequencySync=") and ($radioEquipmentClockReferenceId ne @radioEquipmentClockReferenceId) and ($encapsulation eq @encapsulation)]) eq 0))'> <value-of select="."/> Two or more RadioEquipmentClockReference MOs cannot refer to same NtpFrequencySync MO in attribute encapsulation.</assert> <assert test='every $encapsulation in @encapsulation satisfies contains(@encapsulation, "TimeSyncIO=") or contains(@encapsulation, "FrequencySyncIO=") or (contains(@encapsulation, "BoundaryOrdinaryClock=") and (($encapsulation/@clockType eq 1) or ($encapsulation/@clockType eq 2))) or SLAVE_ONLY_ORDINARY_CLOCK.</assert> </rule> </pattern> </schema>

attribute.name: administrativeState
attribute.description: The administrative state.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause traffic disturbances.

attribute.name: adminQualityLevel
attribute.description: Specifies the quality level value to override the received quality level, if useQLFrom is set to ADMIN_QL for all three telecom options.
attribute.dependencies: If the attribute telecomStandard in the MO class Synchronization is changed, adminQualityLevel will change to the quality level value defined within the selected telecom standard.

attribute.name: availabilityStatus
attribute.description:
The availability status.
It contains details about operationalState.

attribute.name: encapsulation
attribute.description:
Reference to underlying encapsulation.
Underlying encapsulation can be MO type FrequencySyncIO, TimeSyncIO, SyncEthInput, BoundaryOrdinaryClock or NtpFrequencySync.
attribute.dependencies:
Two or more RadioEquipmentClockReference MOs cannot refer to same FrequencySyncIO MO. Two or more RadioEquipmentClockReference MOs cannot refer to same TimeSyncIO MO. Two or more RadioEquipmentClockReference MOs cannot refer to same SyncEthInput MO. Two or more RadioEquipmentClockReference MOs cannot refer to same BoundaryOrdinaryClock MO. Two or more RadioEquipmentClockReference MOs cannot refer to same NtpFrequencySync MO.
Attribute encapsulation of RadioEquipmentClockReference MO can only refer to MO type FrequencySyncIO, TimeSyncIO, NtpFrequencySync, SyncEthInput, or BoundaryOrdinaryClock with either clockType BOUNDARY_CLOCK or SLAVE_ONLY_ORDINARY_CLOCK.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause traffic disturbances. Applicable when reconfiguring from frequency synchronization to time synchronization.

attribute.name: holdOffTime
attribute.description: Time from fault detection to switch of reference.

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: The operational state.

attribute.name: operQualityLevel
attribute.description:
Indicates the quality level used by the process for the synchronization reference selection.
If useQLFrom is set to RECEIVED_QL, the quality level extracted from the underlying reference is indicated. If useQLFrom is set to ADMIN_QL, the quality level specified by the attribute adminQualityLevel is indicated.

attribute.name: priority
attribute.description: Specifies the priority of the synchronization reference.
attribute.dependencies: Two or more RadioEquipmentClockReference cannot have the same priority.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause traffic disturbances. Applicable when breaking following rule: Time synchronization references must have higher priority than frequency synchronization references.

attribute.name: radioEquipmentClockReferenceId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: receivedQualityLevel
attribute.description: Indicates the received quality level for the underlying reference. Note that some types of references lack quality level information.

attribute.name: referenceStatus
attribute.description: The status of a synchronization reference.

attribute.name: syncRefType
attribute.description: Type of synchronization reference.

attribute.name: useQLFrom
attribute.description: Whether quality level received from network or from adminQuality is used.

attribute.name: waitToRestoreTime
attribute.description: Time from fault cease to switch back to reference with higher priority.
